The new species can be distinguished from all other Friesea species by the combination of 8+8 eyes, 6 spine-like chaetae on abdomen VI, absence of capitate chaetae on the abdomen and tibiotarsi and fully developed furcula (stage 1-2). Barcode (mtDNA - COI) sequence is provided.

dataset.title: Dataset 3 - Elasmobranchii
